article.headline: South Florida 78, South Alabama 67
article.story: TAMPA, Fla. (AP) -- Four players scored in double figures for South Florida in a 78-67 victory against South Alabama in the USF Holiday Classic on Monday night. Terrence Leather had 16 points and Bradley Mosley added 14 to lead the Bulls (5-5), who will play New Orleans (6-3) for the championship Tuesday night. Marlyn Bryant scored 13 points and Sam Barber had 12 for South Florida. Malerick Redden had 22 points to lead South Alabama (4-5), which remains winless on the road and undefeated at home. The Jaguars will face Texas-Arlington (4-4) in Tuesday's consolation game. South Florida never trailed after taking a 37-32 halftime lead. The Bulls led by as many as 15 points in the second half, but South Alabama closed to within five on a 3-point basket by Richard Law with 42 seconds left. The Bulls hit 32 of 52 shots (61.5 percent) from the floor and outscored the Jaguars 50-22 in the paint. South Alabama hit only 25 of 70 shots (35.7 percent).
